{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"A plugin whose manifest is missing a required field is rejected before any code from that plugin is executed.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Real failure risk is at the loader boundary where manifest parsing/validation is wired to dynamic module import. A unit test of validation alone can miss regressions where import happens before validation.","test_description":"Create a temp plugin directory with one plugin whose `manifest.json` omits a required field and whose entry module has a visible side effect at top-level (for example, writes a marker file). Run the real loader against that directory. Assert: (1) loader reports manifest validation failure for that plugin, and (2) side-effect marker was never created, proving entry code was not executed.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.22,"Integration":0.74,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When plugin A declares a dependency on plugin B, plugin B's `onLoad` hook is called before plugin A's.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The real failure boundary is dependency graph resolution plus hook invocation ordering across plugin modules. Mocked ordering logic can hide wiring mistakes between resolver and executor.","test_description":"Create temp plugins A and B on disk. B exports `onLoad` that appends `B` to a shared log; A depends on B and appends `A`. Run the real loader and assert the observed hook order is exactly `[B, A]`. Also assert both were loaded once.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.77,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"When two plugins each declare a dependency on the other, the loader reports the cycle and loads neither.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Cycle detection must be validated in the full manifest-read + graph-build + load pipeline. A pure algorithm unit test may pass while the loader still attempts imports due to integration bugs.","test_description":"Create temp plugins A and B where each manifest depends on the other, and each entry module has a top-level side effect marker plus `onLoad` log. Run the real loader. Assert: (1) cycle error includes A<->B (or equivalent cycle path), (2) neither plugin `onLoad` ran, and (3) no entry side effects occurred, proving neither was imported/loaded.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.18,"Integration":0.79,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A plugin's `onLoad` hook is only invoked after the plugin's entry module has been imported and executed.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This depends on real module import/execution order in Node plus loader lifecycle sequencing. Mocking import often hides ordering bugs.","test_description":"Create a plugin whose entry module sets `globalThis.pluginInitFlag = true` at top level, then exports `onLoad` that throws if the flag is not already true. Run the real loader. Assert `onLoad` succeeds and a recorded event sequence is `entry-executed` before `onLoad-called`.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.15,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When a plugin throws an error during its `onLoad` hook, the loader continues initializing the remaining plugins that do not depend on it.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure boundary is error isolation in the dependency-aware execution engine. Unit tests of try/catch logic can miss real scheduling/skip rules across multiple plugins.","test_description":"Create plugins: `Bad` throws in `onLoad`; `Independent` has no dependency on `Bad`; `DependsOnBad` depends on `Bad`. Run the real loader. Assert: (1) error for `Bad` is reported, (2) `Independent` still loads successfully, (3) `DependsOnBad` is skipped/failed due to dependency, not loaded, and (4) loader completes overall run without aborting all plugins.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.16,"Integration":0.8,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
